summary: The document is a declassified communication associated with the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992, dated 27 January 1961. It details operations in Mexico City and Cuba, including an urgent requirement for accommodation addresses in Mexico for agents destined for Cuba by 1 February. The communication also references an individual named Antonio Gomez Duran and efforts to acquire additional PO boxes.
key_findings: The document is part of the records released under the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992.
It details operations or communications involving Mexico City and Cuba.
There is an urgent request for accommodation addresses in Mexico for agents being sent to Cuba.
Mentions an individual, Antonio Gomez Duran, and efforts to secure additional PO boxes.
